HEADWORD: Bitumen process
<hw>Bi*tu"men proc"ess</hw>. <fld>(Photog.)</fld> <def>Any process in
which advantage is taken of the fact that prepared bitumen is rendered
insoluble by exposure to light, as in photolithography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bituminate</ent>⟦br⟧
